3. Basic Structure of a C Program-

Question3- Explain the basic structure of a C program, including headers, main function, comments, data types, and variables. Provide examples.
Answer-
Introduction
C programs follow a structured format that includes headers, functions, variables, and statements.

1. Headers
Explanation

Header files include standard libraries

Provide predefined functions

Example
#include <stdio.h>

